<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,319,597]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,218,319,344]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Notes</emphasis>
. Even though numerous species were recently transferred from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[945,1035,319,344]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[945,1035,319,344]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to new genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A. &amp; Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D." box="[1218,1423,319,344]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="51 - 101" refId="ref27545" refString="Huber, B. A., Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. (2018) The phylogeny of pholcid spiders (Araneae, Pholcidae): a critical evaluation of relationships suggested by molecular data. ZooKeys, 789, 51 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 789.22781" type="journal article" year="2018">
Huber 
<emphasis box="[1298,1356,319,344]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[151,242,356,381]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,242,356,381]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
continues to be by far the most species rich genus in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="World Spider Catalog" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[882,992,356,381]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pholcidae</taxonomicName>
(currently 324 species). Except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1907" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1907" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fragillimus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. fragillimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Strand, E." box="[281,426,391,416]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="107 - 215" refId="ref28697" refString="Strand, E. (1907) Sud- und ostasiatische Spinnen. Abhandlungen der naturforschenden Gesellschaft Gorlitz, 25, 107 - 215, pls. 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1907">Strand, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, all Sri Lankan species belong to only one of over 20 currently recognized species groups in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[181,272,428,453]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,272,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[326,461,428,453]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A. &amp; Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D." box="[474,679,428,453]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="51 - 101" refId="ref27545" refString="Huber, B. A., Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. (2018) The phylogeny of pholcid spiders (Araneae, Pholcidae): a critical evaluation of relationships suggested by molecular data. ZooKeys, 789, 51 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 789.22781" type="journal article" year="2018">
Huber 
<emphasis box="[552,610,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
): the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[742,860,428,453]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis box="[742,860,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This species group is restricted to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,463,488]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[267,381,463,488]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and may represent an ancient faunal element: (1) morphologically, the male genitalia differ dramatically from all other known species of the genus, previously misleading me into creating the new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,367,535,560]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Sihala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,223,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Sihala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[229,367,535,560]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for this clade; (2) molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[752,954,535,560]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="141" refId="ref26630" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis box="[834,890,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) have strongly supported a transfer back to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[151,242,572,597]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,242,572,597]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(formalized in 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A. &amp; Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D." box="[414,612,572,597]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="51 - 101" refId="ref27545" refString="Huber, B. A., Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. (2018) The phylogeny of pholcid spiders (Araneae, Pholcidae): a critical evaluation of relationships suggested by molecular data. ZooKeys, 789, 51 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 789.22781" type="journal article" year="2018">
Huber 
<emphasis box="[491,548,572,597]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) but the sister group of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[921,1039,572,597]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis box="[921,1039,572,597]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group remains unknown.
</paragraph>
